<item>
            <title>[SPARK-29953] File stream source cleanup options may break a file sink output</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-29953</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-20568&quot; title=&quot;Delete files after processing in structured streaming&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-20568&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-20568&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added options to file streaming source to clean up processed files. However, when applying these options to a directory that was written by a file streaming sink, it will make the directory not queryable any more because we delete files from the directory but they are still tracked by file sink logs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we should block the options if the input source is a file streaming sink path (has &quot;_spark_metadata&quot; folder).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
